article.headline: Boilermakers pull away for easy win over Wolverines
article.linkText: Boilermakers pull away for easy win over Wolverines
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (Ticker) -- Erika Valek scored 14 of her 19 points in the second half to lead No. 12 Purdue over Michigan, 72-50, in the second round of the Big Ten tournament Friday.

The Boilermakers (24-5) put together a 16-6 run in the first half and led by 12 points at halftime.  Overall, the club outrebounded the Wolverines by a 43-34 margin and outscored them in the paint, 32-20.

Valek connected on 3-of-4 attempts from 3-point range and
grabbed five rebounds.  Despite shooting just 3-of-10 from the
field, All-Big Ten star Shereka Wright finished with 12 points,
eight rebounds and four assists for Purdue.

Mary Jo Noon added 12 points and eight boards for the
Boilermakers, who will face Iowa in the semifinals on Sunday.

Jennifer Smith finished with 15 points and four rebounds for
Michigan (13-16), which shot just 33 percent from the field
(20-for-61).
